* water that is diverted for the purpose of draining a burial ground.

The Government may provide that the following activities may not be undertaken without prior permission or notification:
* the building or operation of certain kinds of factories, other facilities or other environmentally hazardous activities;
* the discharge of wastewater onto land or into water areas or groundwater;
* the discharge or depositing of solid waste or other solid matter where this is liable to pollute land, water areas or groundwater; and

amount of water used is such that the flow is less than four-fifths of the normal unregulated low flow;
