* the construction of platforms for offshore oil or gas extraction and of anchorages or moorings for such platforms, other than temporary ones, for the purposes of repairs, conversion or some other reason;
* motorways, expressways and other roads with at least four traffic lanes that are not less than ten kilometres in length;
* long-distance railway lines and the construction of at least five kilometres of new tracks for existing long-distance railway lines;
* public navigation channels;
* airports with a runway length of at least 2,100 metres.

The environmental courts shall be the first instance for the hearing of cases concerning:
* environmentally hazardous activities which are application cases within the meaning of chapter 21, section 1 first paragraph;
* water operations and water structures within the meaning of chapter 11 and in the Act (1998:812) Containing Special Provisions concerning Water Operations, with the exception of operations involving land drainage, which shall be examined by the competent county administrative board;
* land drainage which are referred by a county administrative board or reported by a property registration authority in accordance with the Act (1998:812) Containing Special Provisions concerning Water Operations;
* compensation for damage and intrusion pursuant to chapter 28, sections 2 to 5;
* compensation and compulsory public acquisitions referred to in this Code and acquisition in connection with water operations, unless other provision is specifically made;
* compensation for environmental damage and compulsory purchase referred to in chapter 32 and actions relating to prohibitions or precautions referred to in chapter 32, section 12;
* the allocation of joint and several liability between several parties pursuant to chapter 10, sections 6 and 7 at the suit of one of the liable parties;
* the award of prospective fines pursuant to this Code at the petition of the authority that issued the injunction. Section 6 second paragraph of the Prospective Fines Act (1985:206) shall be applicable to injunctions issued subject to a penalty of a fine.

Application cases are cases:
* concerning permits for environmentally hazardous activities referred to in chapter 9, section 6 which, pursuant to the provisions of chapter 9, section 8, shall not be considered by county administrative boards or municipalities;
* concerning permits for water operations referred to in chapter 11, section 9 which shall not be considered by county administrative boards;
* concerning approval pursuant to chapter 11, section 16 of alteration or repair works that have been carried out or of measures taken contrary to existing rules concerning the storage and release of water, where the works or measures do not include land drainage which falls within the jurisdiction of the county administrative board;
* concerning permits referred to in chapter 11 for the removal of a water structure or permit application procedures referred to in chapter 11, section 22;
* concerning extension pursuant to chapter 24, section 2 second paragraph of the time limit for completion or commencement of an activity;
* concerning withdrawal of a permit or prohibition of continued activities pursuant to chapter 24, section 3;
* concerning reviews referred to in chapter 24, sections 5 to 9 and chapter 7, sections 13 to 15 of the Act (1998:812) Containing Special Provisions concerning Water Operations; and
* cases referred to in chapter 7, section 1 of the Act (1998:812) Containing Special Provisions concerning Water Operations.

An application in an application case shall be made in writing. It shall contain:
* any information, drawings and technical descriptions that are necessary for an assessment of the nature and scope of the activity or measure;
* an environmental impact statement pursuant to chapter 6 and information about any consultations that have taken place pursuant to chapter 6, sections 4 to 6;
* any information that is necessary for an assessment of compliance with the general rules of consideration laid down in chapter 2;
* proposals for any protective measures or other precautions that may be necessary in order to prevent or remedy the adverse effects of the activity;
* proposals for control of the activity, and
* a security report in those cases where the Act (1999:381) on Measures to Prevent and Limit the Consequences of Major Chemical Accidents is applicable on the activity.
* a security report in those cases where the Act (1999:381) on Measures to Prevent and Limit the Consequences of Major Chemical Accidents is applicable on the activity.
 In cases relating to water operations, applications shall also contain the following:
* information as to whether or not any properties are affected by the operations and, where applicable, the names and addresses of the owners of the properties and any holders of special rights thereto; and
* a statement of the compensation amounts offered by the applicant to each party to the case, unless it is appropriate to postpone the submission of such information on account of the scope of the operations.
