Any person who infringes any of the following rules, whether deliberately or through negligence, shall be liable to a fine or a term of imprisonment not exceeding six months:
* rules concerning public order issued pursuant to chapter 7, section 30;
* rules concerning the prohibition of animal husbandry issued pursuant to chapter 9, section 11;
* rules issued for the purpose of protecting human health or the environment pursuant to chapter 9, section 12;
* the notification requirement laid down in chapter 11, section 15 third paragraph with respect to works that may be detrimental to fishing;
* rules concerning the management of agricultural land issued pursuant to chapter 12, section 8;
* rules limiting the number of animals on a holding etc. issued pursuant to chapter 12, section 10;
* the prohibition or rules concerning the removal of waste laid down in chapter 15, section 21 by collecting and removing waste professionally or otherwise on a large scale;
